etch what they need.\n\nNext: Probe Endpoint A","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"c6430467-6e2c-6fb5-5581-14c6e229317a","name":"Note: Every Few Minutes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Probe Endpoint A\n\nGET https://service-a.example.com/healthz — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nNext: Combine Probe Results\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,250],"id":"fd797114-106a-11a7-3699-86ed6aec7ddb","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint A"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Probe Endpoint B\n\nGET https://service-b.example.com/healthz — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nNext: Combine Probe Results\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,760],"id":"ea9ba799-2991-032f-8651-0c769d7f861d","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint B"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Probe Endpoint C\n\nGET https://service-c.example.com/healthz — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nNext: Combine Probe Results\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,1270],"id":"af7e7b4d-93e9-c4be-1610-9ca8a3962265","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint C"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Combine Probe Results\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: All Healthy?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,520],"id":"f6b36f15-50c1-ee7c-b3fa-2a3868ed543f","name":"Note: Combine Probe Results"},{"parameters":{"content":"### All Healthy?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ ($json.statusCode || 200) < 400 }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Uptime Metric · ②→ Already Alerted? (State Check)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2262,520],"id":"3d37bb4e-48c7-168e-510c-9b0cba2e1500","name":"Note: All Healthy?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Uptime Metric\n\nnotion — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Serialize Run Output (CSV) · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,280],"id":"1a9d4570-6d4a-1fe4-7948-acc0c7a0d5f4","name":"Note: Record Uptime Metric"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Already Alerted? (State Check)\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Page On-Call via Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,880],"id":"da0d395a-089d-894c-55c5-9fc24ea6a255","name":"Note: Already Alerted? (State Check)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Page On-Call via Slack\n\nmicrosoftTeams — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Microsoft OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,880],"id":"8558cede-cf7a-795d-c965-07a7922aad44","name":"Note: Page On-Call via Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"9a432a7b-0468-965a-184e-1c2fa3ee1889","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Load Previous Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"2958447c-c18b-dbb5-b253-2b4253ae4abb","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `read` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"c15aade1-6996-d610-b350-cda25b971e0e","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"5d9fbe15-2066-9bf7-e6b6-4c7c2d5b9e96","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"815d479b-38e4-a3c1-47ba-e043a84cbda7","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"a1254eab-b59e-5f9a-10d2-56c496331c10","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"4e84bc30-c9ae-addc-02d3-cb743637a5d4","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6798,520],"id":"36e408e6-7476-2555-30d1-94cf162582d9","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7122,520],"id":"a828ec65-c9d4-0c65-6937-90221e8bfd89","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7446,520],"id":"34a93ba4-5319-ebc4-7a38-c463c1208407","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per asset (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7770,520],"id":"fc33be37-aaa6-b232-04ab-e3256c2163d4","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Stamp Processing Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8094,520],"id":"ea0a6930-faca-0342-fe69-757f37d6a7a4","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Processing Time\n\nStamps `processedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8418,520],"id":"d40eb3d6-f48f-2d57-e48d-01ab068eb45d","name":"Note: Stamp Processing Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 100 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8742,520],"id":"0317b3a5-a29f-145e-55ea-02d4fa09de6b","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9066,520],"id":"3ba33897-2cf4-6560-dc7b-36d7babcbb00","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Notion)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,520],"id":"ba12c0fb-be1a-c31e-5805-9cf8873d8767","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Notion)\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,520],"id":"ac644aac-54dd-12fb-e949-4e1166fda28c","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Notion)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10038,520],"id":"5e2d138a-82ab-cf0c-48a7-c8cf6b8aa34e","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,1540],"id":"78c2bb6c-332d-ba4e-aeeb-7221bbc8accb","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,1540],"id":"d2e8df50-8e00-ffd4-23e3-be6c65fb68a5","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10038,1540],"id":"d4911abe-579e-071d-00ad-a58305455ddc","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Alert on spend with HTTP / REST API and Microsoft Teams in real time\n\n**Pattern:** Threshold Monitoring · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nAlert on spend with HTTP / REST API and Microsoft Teams in real time. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual signals is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nEvery Few Minutes → Probe Endpoint A → Combine Probe Results → All Healthy? → Record Uptime Metric → Serialize Run Output (CSV) → Archive Row Snapshot → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to threshold monitoring without manual effort\n- Anyone automating signals in finance\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Standardizes the process every time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"f2744620-4d64-f391-8175-f636b1aa4328","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-290],"id":"edf8812c-b307-d62e-37a5-107cb412de22","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-290],"id":"8817661c-2193-378c-cd42-4719ba4757e6","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your signals process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-290],"id":"8e483a56-a0df-23a3-a64a-d3df9a0098b8","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Every Few Minutes":{"main":[[{"node":"Probe Endpoint A","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Probe Endpoint B","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Probe Endpoint C","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Probe Endpoint A":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Probe Endpoint B":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":1}]]},"Probe Endpoint C":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":2}]]},"Combine Probe Results":{"main":[[{"node":"All Healthy?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"All Healthy?":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Uptime Metric","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Already Alerted? (State Check)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Already Alerted? (State Check)":{"main":[[{"node":"Page On-Call via Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Uptime Metric":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Processing Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Processing Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Notion)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Notion)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Page On-Call via Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"2ef9fb6d-0e6a-45d5-9c9d-68d016785992","id":"FDX08942"}